Package entities

Class User

java.lang.Object
entities.User
public class User extends Object

Just like Event class, this is just a placeholder class for storing Event entity when doing business logic code. Thus all properties are set to public.

This class behaves similarly to a struct in C. The purpose of this class is just for other outside functions to change its state, that's all. No methods, only attributes!

    • User

      User(String name, String password, String email, List<Event> evList, int userID)

      This is a default constructor for making User class.

      Those JsonPropertys are used for deserializing from JSON objects back to User object.

      Parameters:
      name - Name of the user
      email - email of the user. Reminder: this user class is just a placeholder, so it is not responsible for verifying email's format. I wonder if this design decision is correct or not.
      password - password of the user. Reminder: this user class is just a placeholder, so it is not responsible for verifying password's format.
      password - password of the user. Reminder: this user class is just a placeholder, so it is not responsible for verifying password's format. Also the password should ideally be hashed.
      eventList - list of events the user is hosting or participating. Reminder: this eventList absolutely does not reflect the actual event list of the user.
      userID - userID of the user. Reminder: , again this class is just a placeholder, so sometimes we dont even need to specify this ID.
      Throws:
      IOException - if an input or output error is detected when the servlet handles the GET request
      InvalidA - if the request for the GET could not be handled
